# 2. 見守る者達

MEIKO: ...
MEIKO: (That look on Mizuki's face...)
Mizuki: Thanks, MEIKO.
Mizuki: I'm gonna see what I can do about dealing with my own problems.
MEIKO: It seems that time has finally come...
???: Hey.
MEIKO: ...!
MEIKO: What is it...?
KAITO: I have a question about Mizuki.
KAITO: Something didn't seem quite right. You need to tell me if you have any information.
MEIKO: I'm surprised to hear you asking about Mizuki...
KAITO: Mizuki's words have the power to help Mafuyu.
KAITO: Mafuyu needs to hear them in order to move forward.
MEIKO: I agree...
MEIKO: I don't actually have any details...
MEIKO: However, as I told you when you first arrived, we're dealing with some very complicated feelings here...
MEIKO: And it seems that Mizuki is currently setting the stage to face those feelings head-on...
MEIKO: No running this time.
KAITO: I see...
KAITO: But I sensed quite a bit of doubt just now...
KAITO: What exactly is Mizuki afraid of or running from?
MEIKO: I...
MEIKO: I'm not in a position to say...
KAITO: Ugh...
MEIKO: ...! KAITO, wait.
MEIKO: Are you going over to see Mizuki...?
KAITO: Yes.
MEIKO: Please don't.
MEIKO: Mizuki is trying to cross a thin sheet of ice right now.
MEIKO: What you're planning on saying is going to be too strong. So strong that you might make that ice crack...
KAITO: So, you want me to do nothing...?
MEIKO: ...
KAITO: If doing nothing will solve everything, then that's fine by me. But do you honestly believe that's going to bring about real change?
MEIKO: Don't think that your solution is always the best one.
KAITO: Then, tell me yours.
MEIKO: ...
MEIKO: KAITO...!
MEIKO: Wait!!
Mizuki: ...
Mizuki: (I... I still can't send it...)
Mizuki: (But I made the decision to finally tell her...)
Mizuki: I'm so scared...
???: <Hey.>
Mizuki: Huh? Oh...!
Mizuki: KAITO...
Mizuki: What's up? You hardly ever come to see me like this.
KAITO: <I need to talk to you.>
Mizuki: To me...?
KAITO: <What is it that you're...?>
???: <KAITO!>
Mizuki: Huh...?!
MEIKO: <Didn't I tell you to stop...?!>
MEIKO: <You have no right asking such a question!>
Mizuki: M-MEIKO...?
KAITO: <You really feel the need to intervene like this...?>
KAITO: <Fine. But let me at least say this.>
KAITO: <Mizuki. You're stuck at a crossroads, yes?>
Mizuki: ...!
KAITO: <I have no way of knowing what's eating away at you...>
KAITO: <That being said...>
KAITO: <You find yourself at a crossroads because you're trying to make a choice... Because you want to make a choice, not because of anyone else.>
KAITO: <But that goes without saying...>
Mizuki: ...
KAITO: <I don't care if you decide to run or move forward...>
KAITO: <But just know this... In the midst of this pain, you need to choose the path that allows you to save yourself.>
KAITO: <In order to keep on living...>
Mizuki: KAITO...
MEIKO: <...>
MEIKO: <Mizuki.>
MEIKO: <All I can do is watch.>
MEIKO: <But I've witnessed the pain you bear.>
MEIKO: <I've been right there.>
Mizuki: MEIKO...
MEIKO: <I honestly believe that you shouldn't try to do anything...>
MEIKO: <Because what you're carrying...is so incredibly fragile.>
Mizuki: ...
MEIKO: <But...>
MEIKO: <I'll see this through with you. No matter how things turn out.>
MEIKO: <Regardless of how the future unfolds, I'll be there with you until the end.>
Mizuki: Oh...
Mizuki: *Nod*
Mizuki: Thanks, you two.
Mizuki: But...
Mizuki: I... I just need a little bit more time...
